prompt: Create a detailed medical decision-making flowchart illustrating the surgical approach selection in acute mesenteric ischemia. LAYOUT: Landscape orientation, flowchart flowing from TOP to BOTTOM. STARTING POINT (top center): Large rectangular box labeled "ACUTE MESENTERIC ISCHEMIA - CONFIRMED DIAGNOSIS" with a red medical cross icon. FIRST DECISION (below): Diamond-shaped decision box asking "PERITONITIS PRESENT?" with green border. LEFT BRANCH (YES): Bold red arrow pointing LEFT then DOWN to red-bordered action box "IMMEDIATE OPEN SURGERY - Laparotomy Required" with scalpel icon. This branches to "Assess Bowel Viability" then "Revascularize if Possible" then "Resect Necrotic Bowel". RIGHT BRANCH (NO): Blue arrow pointing RIGHT then DOWN to blue-bordered box "ASSESS HEMODYNAMIC STATUS". SECOND DECISION from right branch: Diamond asking "HEMODYNAMICALLY STABLE?" YES leads to "CONSIDER ENDOVASCULAR APPROACH" (blue path). NO leads to "RESUSCITATE THEN REASSESS" (yellow path with fluid bag icon). ENDOVASCULAR branch continues: "CT Angiography Review" → "Anatomically Suitable?" decision → "PROCEED WITH ENDOVASCULAR" or "OPEN SURGERY RECOMMENDED". Include "HYBRID APPROACH" option branching from middle. VISUAL STYLE: Clean professional medical infographic, white background, modern sans-serif fonts. Color coding: RED for surgical urgency, BLUE for endovascular pathway, YELLOW for monitoring steps, GREEN for positive outcomes. All arrows must have clear arrowheads pointing in the direction of flow. Rounded rectangles for actions, diamonds for decisions. High resolution suitable for medical education materials. NO embedded text labels - use placeholder boxes where labels would go.
